i25{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:100%;display:block;margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;font-family:Arial;color:black;font-size:16px;line-height:2;}#header0{height:auto;min-height:auto;width:100%;display:block;padding-right:20px;padding-left:20px;margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;}#header1{background-color:rgb(152,213,218);height:auto;min-height:5px;width:100%;display:block;position:relative;margin:15px auto;}#header2{background-color:white;height:auto;min-height:25px;width:100%;display:block;position:relative;padding:10px;margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;text-align:center;}#header3{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:auto;display:inline-block;padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;margin-right:15px;margin-left:15px;font-family:Raleway;color:black;font-size:16px;}#header4{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:auto;display:inline-block;padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;margin-right:15px;margin-left:15px;font-family:Raleway;color:black;font-size:16px;}#header5{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:auto;display:inline-block;padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;margin-right:15px;margin-left:15px;font-family:Raleway;color:black;font-size:16px;}#header6{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:auto;display:inline-block;padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;margin-right:15px;margin-left:15px;font-family:Raleway;color:black;font-size:16px;}#header7{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:auto;display:inline-block;padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;margin-right:15px;margin-left:15px;font-family:Raleway;color:black;font-size:16px;}#header8{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:auto;display:inline-block;padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:5px;margin-right:15px;margin-left:15px;font-family:Raleway;color:black;font-size:16px;}#header{background-color:white;height:auto;min-height:50px;width:100%;position:relative;padding-top:15px;padding-bottom:15px;margin-top:25px;}#footer_separator{background-color:rgb(208,203,191);height:auto;min-height:50px;width:100%;position:relative;padding:10px;}#footer0{background-color:inherit;height:auto;width:100%;font-family:Arial;color:black;font-size:14px;line-height:1;cursor:text;}#footer{background-color:white;height:auto;min-height:27px;width:100%;position:relative;padding:15px;margin-bottom:15px;}body{background-image:url('images/fiber_background.jpg');}@media(min-width: 768px){.container{width:750px;}#i14,#i19,#i21,#i23,#i25,#i27,#i29,#i11{width:100%;}#i15{width:25%;}#header0{width:333px;}#header1{width:100%;}#header2{width:97.47%;}}@media(min-width: 992px){.container{width:970px;}#i11{width:70%;}#i14{width:78%;}#i15{width:20%;}#i21,#i23,#i25,#i27,#i29,#i19{width:80%;}#header1{width:80%;}#header2{width:967px;}}@media(min-width: 1200px){.container{width:1170px;}}</style><link defer="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"></head><body><div class="container"><div id="header"><a href="index.php"><div id="header0"><img src="images/the_tattered_daisy_logo.png" style="width: 100%; height: 100%;"></div></a><div id="header1"></div><div id="header2"><div id="header3"><a href="index.php" style="text-decoration: none;">HOME</a></div><div id="header4"><a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/thetattereddaisy" style="text-decoration: none;" target="_blank">SHOP</a></div><div id="header5"><a href="custom_orders.php" style="text-decoration: none;">CUSTOM ORDERS</a></div><div id="header6"><a href="gallery.php" style="text-decoration: none;">GALLERY</a></div><div id="header7"><a href="about.php" style="text-decoration: none;">ABOUT</a></div><div id="header8"><a href="contact.php" style="text-decoration: none;">CONTACT</a></div></div></div><div id="i10"><div id="i11"><div id="i12">CUSTOM ORDERS </div><div id="i13"></div><div id="i14">Custom quilts are a Tattered Daisy specialty. Whether you already have a design in mind, or are looking for a little inspiration, I will guide you step by step through the quilting process. The result will be a one-of-a-kind treasure. To start planning a custom quilt, <a href="contact.php"><u>contact me</u></a>. To view my work, visit my <a href="gallery.php">gallery.</a></div><div id="i15"><div id="i16"><img src="images/custom_orders_rainy_day_quilt.jpg" data-pin-nopin="true" style="width: 100%; height: auto;" width="0" height="0"></div></div><div style="clear: both;"></div><div id="i17">See what others are saying about their Tattered Daisy experience:</div><div id="i18"></div><div id="i19"><div>My husband absolutely loves his new/old quilt!! At first he didn't believe that they were all of his old camp shirts. He said it looks so perfect and seamless that he thought it was silk screened or printed somehow! He loves it and says it's the coolest, most special gift that he's ever received! The quilt is beautiful! It was such a fun project and process to work with you. This is something that will stay in our family forever and one day our kids will be able cuddle up with it by the fire at summer camp! Thank you so much!</div><div><br></div><div style="text-align: right;"><i>- Taleen</i></div><div style="text-align: right;"><i>Tustin, CA</i></div></div><div id="i20"></div><div id="i21"><span style="line-height: 2; background-color: inherit;">I ordered two custom quilts from The Tattered Daisy and they were absolutely beyond beautiful! First of all, I don't have a creative bone in my body so I had no idea what to ask for material or pattern wise. After meeting with Stacy I decided to let her have complete control! Wow, what an amazing job! Several of the jerseys I had were "difficult" vests with buttons and no sleeves, however, Stacy was able to utilize these by making them into matching pillows! Both my sons have played baseball since pre-T-Ball. I saved their jerseys knowing that I'd like them to have them some day. I gave them each a quilt when they graduated high school. It's been a long time since I've seen my teenage sons' faces light up opening a present!!! Priceless!</span><div style="text-align: right;"><i>- Lisa</i></div><div style="text-align: right;"><i>Anaheim, CA</i></div></div><div id="i22"></div><div id="i23"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-color: inherit;">My journey with Stacy began because of the death of a feisty 14-year-old red-head who spent her brief years of life showing all of us how to make a difference -- and why we should. </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-color: inherit;">Her Mom hoped a T-shirt quilt could be created from the shirts that her sweet girl had worn - and rocked - in her last years with us. A few phone calls and inquiries led me to Stacy and the Tattered Daisy. I know the red-head was driving this journey.</span><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">After some initial phone conversations, I met with Stacy in person, T-shirts in hand. She was sensitive, compassionate, and kind as we went through the shirts. We talked about which shirts worked best and why, which ones had challenges, and which ones made us laugh.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">I gave this irreplaceable collection from a life to Stacy – and I left. Stacy began her magic.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">Many emails were exchanged as the fabric went from being garments worn, to being blocks arranged into an artful assembly and reflection of our little red-head – a quilt that Mom could wrap up in and be hugged.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">Stacy was the miracle worker that I needed to pull off this project for my dear friend. Always friendly, caring, and professional, Stacy was thoughtful and focused as she listened to my requests. She was beyond patient with my ever changing ideas mid-stream for the quilt, and would gently guide me to the best choice given all the factors. She cut no corners except with scissors where necessary. She was quick to return a phone call or reply to an email. There are many stages and steps to building a quilt--- I always felt in-the-loop. There were no surprises – except the amazing ones. Frequent updates of progress with photos attached to show options, made the process an experience. Stacy brings to her craft the highest hand-made quality you can imagine, and her expertise is impeccable. The finished creation left us all nearly speechless and in tears. The quilt we received was light years beyond anything we had imagined –and the creation experience had been filled with Joy, Artistry, Love, and Creativity.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">Stacy is a gift to all who find her, and anadditional gift to those who use her talents. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">All of this from a red-head, a stack of T-shirts,and a wish from a Mom. Wishes do come true.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">With profound gratitude -- </span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: right;"><span style="line-height: 18.4px;"><i>- Becky</i></span><i style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-color: inherit;"> </i></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;"><i>Pasadena, CA</i></span></p></div><div id="i24"></div><div id="i25">"Stacy made two custom baby quilts for me and I was thrilled with the results! Excellent work, met my deadlines for both baby showers, and gave me lots of examples and fabric choices. I cannot wait to work with her again in the future."<div style="text-align: right;"><i>- Deana</i></div><div style="text-align: right;"><i>Irvine, CA</i></div></div><div id="i26"></div><div id="i27">"Stacy put a lot of care, thought and planning into the design of the custom quilt I ordered; she made it a very special and personalized gift. She has a great talent for matching just the right design to fit the tastes and style of the recipient. It was a pleasure working with her. She made the process very easy and fun, showing pictures and giving updates along the way. I was very excited to see the finished product — it was top quality work. It met my expectations and more! The recipient loves it and is enjoying her heirloom treasure! I will definitely be ordering future gift items. Thank you, Stacy!"<div style="text-align: right;"><i>- Linda</i></div><div style="text-align: right;"><i>Martinez, CA</i></div></div><div id="i28"></div><div id="i29">"In typical last minute fashion, I got the bright idea in mid–December to provide my Mom the most memorable Christmas gift I could muster — a memory quilt. Earlier in the year, our tight knit family had lost our matriarch (my Grandma) after 92 years of love and life. Therefore, I wanted the gift for my grieving mom to be most special. I searched the internet and called dozens of local shops and was eventually referred to Stacy. She was immediately responsive and professional. But more importantly, she moved heaven and earth to complete the most beautiful tear–soliciting quilt in time for Christmas. Yes, in time for Christmas! From shopping with her for fabrics, to photo placement and transfer, to finishing techniques, Stacy was incredible! I simply cannot say enough positives about her, her creativity, tenacity, responsiveness, and most apparent passion. Don't waste your time or your treasures elsewhere, call Stacy now!"<div style="text-align: right;"><i>- Britta</i></div><div style="text-align: right;"><i>Yorba Linda, CA</i></div></div></div></div><div id="footer_separator"></div><div id="footer"><div id="footer0">Copyright © The Tattered Daisy 2016</div></div></div><script type="text/javascript">document.body.onload = deferFonts;setTimeout(deferFonts, 2000);function deferFonts() { var defer = document.querySelectorAll("[defer]"); for (var i = 0; i < defer.length; i++) { defer[i].setAttribute("href", defer[i].getAttribute("defer")); }}</script><script type="text/javascript"></script></body></html>